reviews.text: Went to see Charlotte's Web for a preschool field trip. The ushers were very well organized and got us to our seats with our school quickly. The organist was outstanding! The kids had fun dancing to his music until the show started. The play was great. The actors were very engaging and the kids really enjoyed the show. The theater is beautiful and well maintained. Very clean and brings you back to "the old days" - a great theater experience!

Incredible! What an amazing space...saw Amos Lee here which was just spectacular! He was great! The venue was great! The staff was great! Parking is close and a walk around downtown after the show was great too. The sound was much better than I thought it might be as well for the age of the building.

Beautiful theater. Has the decor that reminds you of the Fox or other historical sites, but on a smaller scale. (I am a short person and my knees were hitting the seats in front of me, so definitely not a lot of leg room.) Sound quality was good, we saw a comedy act.

Loved seeing Randy Rainbow at the Michigan Theater. He was great and the venue was perfect. I wondered if I would be able to hear in the balcony. No worry. I heard it all. Of course he also had subtitles with the lyrics.

The theater itself is really quite beautiful. There isn't much leg room between rows so keep that in mind if you're tall. I don't know whether it had something to do with the venue itself, but the crowd at the show I saw here was by far the most disrespectful crowd I've seen for any concert. People were entering and leaving the auditorium in droves throughout the show, forcing ushers to direct them to their seats with flashlights the entire time, creating quite a distraction from the show. Definitely a mixed bag for my visit, but it's hard to really attribute that to the venue itself.

As a newbie to visiting Ann Arbor, I think this place is an absolute gem. The staff consists of mostly volunteers and is helpful and friendly. It is an intimate setting which makes a concert or a show experience very different, in a positive way! Solid drink menu with reasonable prices. You do have to be a member to purchase drinks, or be a guest of a member.
Ann Arbor's music spot. It resonates with the right frequencies on several tones at once - harmony rings here! And it's right next to Blue Llama, the new jazz spot!

I absolutely love the Ark. Friendly staff (non profit organization) but they do not let that change the level of service at all! 
Great lighting, sound was great as well. Seating was perfect for a personal "coffee house" feeling. I would say it's now in my top 5 favorite places. 

William Fitzsimmons & Jim and Sam, Mission Bell Tour 2018. A fabulous set
Folk and indie music heaven. Intimate venue for enjoying vastly underappreciated talent and without killing your budget. One of the top 5 things about Ann Arbor.
I love live music, especially in smaller venues. The Ark is wonderful with great acts coming through more than 300 nights each year.

Happiest little place on earth. Everyone should experience the big house atmosphere at least once. Had the pleasure of going to a night game this past season and the place was rocking. Totally different experience than a day game. That being said, doing a little tailgating, throwing around the football and spending the afternoon cruising around Ann Arbor and going to a Michigan game is just about the perfect Saturday.

Massive on the inside...understandable being "The Big House". Great views of the field. Enough bathrooms so that the lines are not too excessive at halftime. A lot of vendors around the perimeter. Watching and waving at the mobile field camera is fun as well. Bring something soft to sit on if you have normal tickets...just check the website first to make sure you are allowed to bring it into stadium first.

As a big Michigan Football fan. I genuinely enjoy attending the games with my husband. The stadium is always clean and we've yet to come across any issues. Concessions staff are always friendly and security staff are helpful. Highly recommend seeing a game at The Big House!!!
This is a great stadium. All of the seats are good. We sat in the corner of the second level and had great views.
No place like the Big House for a football game. largest stadium in the country. if you ever get the chance to watch a game here jump on it, you will remember the experience forever.

I am sorry that this message I wrote may disturb you(I'm sorry I am poor English). I only wish leave this message for my best friend here, "The cutest girl, we will meet,  we will go to UMich together." - A boy living Dayton, OH.

I didn't go here, but visited the campus. The library is something straight out of Harry Potter. It's beautiful, and you can really feel the school spirit. I think the students, faculty, and anyone associated with the school is proud of it.

On 10/12/18 Michigan Tour guide Raoul seems to dislike "rich white men that donate 100 million dollars" to build a business school.  Does it matter what skin color a man has Raoul?  I thought you would not judge a man by his skin color or by how much money he has.  What a poor representative to such an allegedly prestigious University.
Possibly the worst guidance counselors. The campus is overrated and filled with rather pretentious staff and students. The Dearborn branch is better with welcoming professors and students.

In the first place, Michigan remains a top-rated public university. It has many stellar departments, and your degree will open doors anywhere from social work to engineering to medicine. When I was there, the campus was nice and spacious. There are also many extra-curricular opportunities  including football, Greek life and volunteering. However, Michigan is not for everyone. If you like a more intimate, hometown college feel, you may not prefer this school. On the other hand, if you are a self-starter and a second-generation college student, you will do fine. 
 Navigating U of M's serpentine class scheduling and financial aid systems as a first-generation college student would have been a nightmare. As an out-of-state student, I regret not seeking more grants and scholarships, otherwise I had a great experience at U of M.

The doctor's and nurses are totally AWESOME here. I had the best care ever.  I had bladder sling surgery done and Dr. Stoffel did an AMAZING JOB. Thank you so much to the whole staff of doctor's and nurses. Go Blue!!

Great area for walks, relaxing, taking kids, or jogging.  There is a variety of path types, and many connections to other paths and trails in the area.  This is a favorite place to visit, and is nice all times of the year.  We most recently took our daughter on a hike in the winter, and are looking forward to showing her more as she grows older.

I visit here at least 1-2 week with my doggo. We (and especially he) loves it. Beautiful space with lots of winding trails and some formal gardens (love the peonies!) Only concerns are: at times it is very busy and somewhat noisy. Some people play music off of their phones, or large gaggles of college kids meander about, sometimes there's drones, and often the hospital helicopters are standing by or flying. Lastly, the train: it's not fenced off, is very loud and I get worried doggo will bolt and jump on front of it. Maybe I'm paranoid, but what u gonna do. Still love it!

I actually gave this place 7 stars...don't pass up the arb!!!  Peaceful, beautiful,  inspiring are some of the best ways to describe it.   Come take a  hike, bird watch, kayak,  lounge, and enjoy friends and family.  Dog friendly with a wonderful peony garden that will leave you speechless in full bloom.  4 seasons of wonderful views and sights.
Very peaceful place to unwind after a day of studying. Lots of trails. Good for families and dogs, terrain isn't difficult.

Personally, I think the selection of pieces of art are beautiful and encompass a variety of styles, techniques, colors, themes, so anybody could find a piece he or she likes.
However, the website of Ave María Fine Art Gallery, could be better designed including more information about the artists whose pieces are exhibit.

This is a great place with a wonderful desert biome. There are many species of cactus as well as some very beautiful flowers.  The staff is very knowledgeable and after noticing a photo exhibit that they currently had I asked if they ever have exhibitions where they ask for submissions and was told that they do and that you do not need to be vetted you can be a normal person who has taken a great picture.   I hope you enjoy a couple that I took the other day.

Would have been 5 but it's winter and we didn't get full effect. Would have liked to see more info about the plants than just the names. They could possibly set up a plant selling area by the gift shop. Was a great day in all for my wife and I. We went for her birthday. We will go back with the kids when its warm and in full bloom.

Wonderful. Such a fantastic cross selection of plants. I absolutely LOVE to walk the gardens in spring and summer ane the tropical plants inside make me feel like I'm bk home in the Keys. Just lovely, inside and out! A great way to spend time on rainy and/or sunny days!
One of my favorite places in town. Great for photography and still life drawing. Last time I was there they had some wonderful art on exhibit as well!

Definitely worth stopping in! Very friendly and knowledgeable staff. The conservatory is amazing with different sections,  very unique plants! I love walking the trails along the creek and the grounds are very interesting to walk through too.  They often host various events, most focused on kids and education.
Give it a spin! Careful not to let it hit you, though!
The Cube is nice.... But it's blocked of. Surrounding area have construction going on.
Give it a spin !
A true Ann Arbor land Mart

Always a fun and quick stop.

Run, run, run to spin the cube - no matter how old you are!
Spin in the summer at Art Fair, Spin during football season, and especially Spin while the students are away during Winter Break.

Watch little kids around the cube, it is heavy and could really knock a noggin' if your little one is left unattended!
Took my 7 year old, he thought it was so cool. I love that there's a place like this close enough to me

Big a big art fan myself I enjoy casually strolling the alley, checking out all of the dope pieces people create. My biggest let down is the amount of pan handlers and junkies that kind of use the alley as a hide out on less busier days
Unique slice of Ann arbor with a gum wall and graffiti. Worth a visit if in the area for the kitsch.
Great display of street art! Iconic Ann Arbor destination.
Such a fun little place.  Took senior photos here and they're fantastic.

Extremely helpful staff! They seem to want to get to the heart of your problems/projects without being pushy. They are also really collaborative about solutions. Definitely, go here instead of the Ace near by. Prices are also fair. I'm new to the area and this will be a go to place for me now.

Get your locks re-keyed here!! All the staff here is very attentive and willing to help. 

My re-key experience: I unscrewed three locks from my new house and brought them here after not having any luck with other local locksmiths being open on the weekend, and certain large chains only offering to re-key locks if you bought them from their store. When I walked in, a staff member was more than willing to assist me with my request. The work took about 15-20 minutes to be done overall, which, in my opinion, is really fast! But the most amazing thing is THE PRICE! I paid $5 per lock, which is SUPER cheap compared to the prices I was quoted by other places. 

All-in-all, I will definitely be giving Stadium Hardware more of my business in the future! Their customer service is up there with some of the best I've ever experienced.
Excellent store to try first. They have all sorts of items that can't be found in other hardware stores. The staff are very professional, helpful & extremely courteous.

Excellent local hardware store! The shelves are filled with the most comprehensive array of products I have ever seen in a small store, and the staff is incredibly helpful and friendly. Highly recommended for any and all hardware needs, obscure and otherwise.

The owners take personal investment in your project and will guide you to the most cost effective option and ensure you have everything you need. The people working here are impossibly nice and helpful.

This pool is great for the whole family. I give it four stars however because they could expand to add a slide like the other main public pools in A2. Also, it would be helpful if they allowed kids under 2 to be in the water during adult swim so parents of very young children had a chance to get in the larger pool with young ones without the fear of them getting jumped on, splashed, etc. (Rutherford in Ypsi allows this and it's great)

Great little kids pool with fun gadgets for them to play with. Kids have to get out of the pools for 15 min every hour for an adult-only swim. Can lead to tears but also great time to get kids to leave.

Ok pool. Don't really like the locker area. The life guards. They also let too many kids at once I to there. Sometimes two different camps come at the same time and it is terribly unsafe to be in the water with your kids. It is ok on a day when there are less kids but you never know when that is going to happen. The little toddler are is nice and my kids enjoy that a lot.
We had to clear out of the pool because of the weather but the staff was awsome! They offered us games and treats while we were waiting for the storm to pass!
We like this pool for little kids best of all the ann arbor pools. The separate kid area is perfect for little ones and doesn't generally get too crowded.
Love the artrain
Interesting to see how the Kempf family lived. Great staff! Very knowledgeable.

A Presidential LIBRARY. Remember that the President Form MUSEUM is not here; it's in Grand Rapids MI. Most people assume the two facilities are co-located, and Ford's are not. As a Presidential library, this is a great facility with material, research rooms, and related space; BUT it also has some conference and meeting rooms, and there's a small amount of view-able, "museum-like" material as well. A Presidential library a lot like Ford himself: low-key and functional but with some nice touches that enhance things.

This was great as a short stop while in town for another reason. The facility was clean, accessible, and interesting. Lots of documents and small exhibits that were really interesting to look over. If you're interested in history at all, I would definitely recommend planning an hour to visit.
Super informative and historical. Great use of picture displays.

It was great to see documented, the humble sincerity of a great leader. Sometimes we get so much misconception from tv comedies that sight is lost to the true character of a man who did so much. Unselfish, and without any egotistic agenda
Great information
This is probably one my favorite museums EVER. Worth the trip. I saw so many interesting things and loved watching the scientists. My entire family had a great time.
Beautifully done revision! The new museum is displaying some exhibits that the old museum couldn't due to lack of space.  Well done, U of M!

super cool place to visit if you are in ann arbor. Budget  friendly. They have everything  from rocks and minerals, dinosaurs, animals, and space exhibits  in such a pretty  building. This is a great stop for a family  day

Update question: will the new museum have a KID friendly plannaterium or will they be just as rude to kids as they always have been? 

We like the museum but the planetarium I want to warn you is NOT kid friendly or shall say the people giving presentations. My 5 year old was completely amazed by it, I wouldn’t have brought him in if he was loud to disrupt anyone, he said ooh wow cool in a normal talking not loud voice because he was amazed by it and the rude guy presenting scolded him twice to be quiet that it’s disruptive and s third time he signaled to my son to zip it again when he was whispering to me to look at something that interested him so my son couldn’t be excited to learn here and couldn’t even whisper.. actually the presenter was louder when scolding my son so he was the one being disruptive. Apparently kids can’t go in and be amazed at what they see or well express it for that matter. It’s not like he was acting up, screaming or throwing a tantrum because I would have walked him out if he was plus he wasn’t continuously talking which we understood plus he understood not to talk when someone else is talking but a quick expression of excitement a couple times from a child is to be expected.  I think this was the worst experience we have had here and won’t be back because of it. Kids can’t be excited to learn here which is sad. Here is a tip, don’t hire people who are not kid friendly. We were sitting closest to the man presenting at the time which is why he was able to hear him at all.  After the show we had a couple other people approach us and complimented how adorable our son was and that it was great as to how amazed he was and how rude the student was giving the presentation. Why is this even acceptable here?

He really has his heart set on working for NASA when he gets big and sure he may change his mind as many and most do but kids shouldn’t have their love for something crushed due to some uptight people. I would love if someone could contact me about this issue.. to make it known this review was noticed by someone at the museum would be little more comforting maybe
There are big windows looking right in to observe the scientists working on huge jaw bones and other skeletons. Very cool! Worth visiting.
There's not much sightseeing in Ann Arbor. So you could have spent a whole afternoon there, if you are interested in history and culture. Well presented and it's free.

Excellent museum.  Officially free, but well worth the suggested donation if you can afford it.  They make superb use of available space.  They have regularly scheduled tours available, but the information plaques included with the displays make the tour a bonus instead of a requirement.

Phenomenal collection and very educated staff. The Kelsey collection is so large that everything isn't showcased at once. There's an actual child mummy, and a replica room from a building recovered in Pompeii. The museum is definitely a 'must see' if you are visiting the Ann Arbor area.
I had a fun time when I went here. Gift shop is a little weak, and the museum is admittedly small, but I found it to be interesting and a stop worth seeing. Especially in winter.
Really liked the artifacts! It was cool to learn something new. Unfortunately, not sure if it would satisfy children.

If only in 1800s our government agreed to allow dentistry to be considered medical. Who would have knew our mouth are the most important portal for our body.
It's a truly magnificent collection! Touring the facility, learning, and viewing the moon through the Victorian telescope is a very enriching experience.

Wonderful experience. Beautiful building even from the outside but a real treat to be inside such a historic building, with very knowledgeable and friendly guides. Clear skies meant a viewing through the 17ft Fitz Refractor.
Actual Victorian era telescope right on main campus. An interesting experience. Very friendly guides.
Pretty cool. Historic. They'll still let you use the original telescope when the weather is nice. So check the schedule. Definitely worth a  quick stop if you're nearby.

I didn't go here, but visited the campus. The library is something straight out of Harry Potter. It's beautiful, and you can really feel the school spirit. I think the students, faculty, and anyone associated with the school is proud of it.

Delightful place,  fresh and yummy cusine. Pot of tea is standard the minute you sit down. One of my happy places.
Nice staff, good food, good prices. Pleasant and quiet most times, even during lunch time.

This place is not good. I ordered chicken and basil, as well as a $10, or more order of vegetables, for a total cost of approx $40 after tax and tip. Nevertheless, I received some chicken bones and fatty tissue, and veggies drowned in sauce. I cannot recommend this place at all.
Fast and delicious. Crab rangoons are hot and tasty!
When they say spicy they mean spicy. The Spicy Szechuan Fish made my eyes water, my nose run. It'll give my dog heartburn if he drinks out of the toilet! But it was wonderful!

Very nice bagel shop! I read about them in a local newspaper and decided to stop. The bagels were excellent! I also purchased a Fragel and thought it was good also. They will be moving by the end of December. So please go.

Bagel Fragel is a beloved institution here. But their rent has been arbitrarily raised and they are searching for a new location. I really love Bagel Fragel and I hope they relocate to be very close to my home so I can go there frequently.
Love bagel fragel they have a great selection of bagels and cream cheese, Their smoothies are delicious I recommend the strawberry one sad to see this place close but hope it re-opens soon.
Great place, but sadly today is its last day as they are closing due to Ann Arbor commercial real estate prices.
The fragels are amazing.  It's a shame the landlord is giving them the boot.  Get your travel soon!!!!

I was pleasantly surprised how good the food is here! It is a modest store front but don't let it fool you! The pizza is great, you can taste the freshness. Sooo much better than the big chain companies. The pasta was amazing! 12$ and you get a giant serving, enough for four bowls of pasta with garlic knots and a side salad. Highly recommend the napoletana linguine. Service was great too. They went out of their way to provide extra napkins and side of ranch.

Based on online reviews and its close proximity to my hotel, I ordered delivery during my stay in Ann Arbor.  I ordered a half Greek salad and an Italian sausage pizza.  The salad was pure perfection!  I highly recommend it.  The pizza was also very good (I enjoyed leftovers the next day, too).  I took off one star because the delivery didn't include napkins or utensils.  I mean, I'm staying in a hotel--do you really expect me to have these things readily on hand?  I had to go down to the front desk and request a plastic fork so I could eat my salad.  You guys have great food, so please don't forget the little things that travelers in hotels need.  :)

Just get pizza from this place. Chicken or Pasta is waste of money. Pizza is the best. Do not dine in. Order to go. Bathroom is horrible. They have cleaning problem. The lady who run the place trying her best she is nice. But they need to spend money on the place.

I don't know how this place has so many good reviews. I tried them for the first time last night and will not return. I stopped in for carryout pizza by the slice for my boyfriend and me. First of all, the layout of the restaurant is dysfunctional. The kitchen/working area is so small, I don't know how the three employees were able to move around. And that's another thing. The floor behind the counter has plastic pallets on it and the employees were walking around on the pallets. It was one of the strangest things I've ever seen in a pizza place. The cash register is on a small counter where other customers were just standing around waiting for their orders, so it was impossible to try to place my order and pay. After forcing my way to the register, I ordered two cheese and two pepperoni slices. The cashier could barely figure out how to price them. Cheese and pepperoni are the most basic thing you can order! There were two other customers waiting for their orders and the staff was clearly confused who was supposed to get what order. The employees were running around manically and acting like they could barely comprehend what was going on in the store with three customers! I also noticed there was no hand washing going on as food was being handled. No employee had a clear designated spot to work. They were all just doing whatever. Who manages like that? When I finally received my order they only gave me three slices. I repeated my order of two cheese and two pepperoni. A few minutes later I received my order in a small box and thought to myself "how in the world are there four slices of New York style pizza in here? Did the employee stack them on top of each other?" I was so annoyed I walked out to my car, opened the box, and guess what? Three slices of pizza stacked on top of each other. Unbelievable is all I could think. And who stacks pizza on top of each other? I walked back in and told them my order was still wrong.  A different employee took a slice of cheese pizza, threw some pepperoni on top, and put it in the oven. This is weird, right? Then she pulled it out of the oven and told me to have a great night in an extremely phony voice. She didn't even apologize for the poor service. When I was a teenager, I worked at Cottage Inn, a restaurant with a very large menu and variety of items. I could run the register, take orders, and make all the food by myself on a busy night. It might be hard, but I could certainly handle it on my own. This place can't even get pizza by the slice right with two attempts and three employees working. I was extremely embarrassed for them and would hate to see what it's like when they're actually busy. The pizza was mediocre. Try at your own risk!

My husband liked their pizza a lot and ordered from them dozens of times we recently moved and are now 4 miles away if you view the longest google map route. We have had them deliver before as the route max time also shows as 9 minutes after placing our order and waiting over 30 minutes we received a call back saying we are too far and they will not deliver to us, this woman is the same rude woman we have spoken to before. We were told it would be arriving in 45 minutes when we placed our order and gave our address and he took our payment information as usual. The correct thing to do would have been to call and apologize call back explain they would still deliver our order but in the future they will no longer deliver. She also stated we are over 6 miles away which is not true no matter what route you take. She said it's just too far and did not offer any apology. This is very expensive for what you get- we are dissapointes with our experience and would not recommend this and will be going to many of the other 50 pizza options instead from now on.

This place is great. Friendly service, tasty food, awesome location, and it has a super cool vibe. BTB is definitely by far one of my favorite restaurants in the area. They’re also open well into the early hours of the morning which is a HUGE plus for me, considering most places are closed when I get out of work and am starving. I suggest the Fire and Ice!

The burritos are tasty, and the staff is friendly enough. Although, it is more of a college hangout for frat boys and girls where they can get a quick meal up to the wee hours. When I got there, the door was blocked by college students. Since, the space is so small, I had to stand tucked in the corner to wait for my burrito. Plus, the chick that took my order didn't have the best customer service. I was greeted or given any recommendations.

Came tonight with a group of six and the folks here we extremely professional and served us pretty quickly while still taking care of other customers. My first time having a chimichanga and it was amazing!

Went here at 3 am and the food was great! Got a giant steak burrito and ate it for two separate meals it was huge lol. I recommend them and their churros were really good as well. Great place to get stuff to eat at night since they are open till 4am.
Good size burritos at a good price. This place is better than taco bell at 2 a.m

Very pretty restaurant and plating. Food is somewhat tasteless though, and they like to use this odd, very sweet butter in everything. I got the Eggs Benedict - although it's pretty, you'd find a much better tasting one for less at Angelo's or somewhere else. Potatoes are also a strange texture (and taste), a mix of grainy and wet, almost as if you had sand packaged in some potato skin.
Great spot for brunch if you want to avoid the usual crowds. $5 mimosas and solid options. Had perhaps the best waffles of my life this morning.
Great French vibe and lovely seating. Usually pretty empty. Lovely wait staff and good wine.
Pleasant atmosphere, good service. Nice variety on the brunch menu. Good coffee, though it could be hotter

This restaurant used to be one of my favorites in graduate school, but today it's just not the same. The food is mediocre and over cooked. I'm not sure if they have a new owner or chef or both, but there are better restaurants on Main Street.

Lovely service. Had the hot bar Sunday am & the frittata was so delicious! Coffee was so delicious.  Used a card & couldn't leave a tip but I was really happy with the service & self serve amenities.  Definitely will be back.
Their bowl of soup is excellent and reasonably priced. Comes with a slice of bread. Best deal in town.
Very kind staff and great coffee and food. Nice atmosphere too.

I enjoy coming here on a Sunday after my yoga class for a matcha latte and a lemon cranberry muffin. I highly recommend both food items. I removed a star because there is only one person working there and while he's nice, he isn't fast and efficient with taking and producing orders. When the line gets long, expect an even longer wait.
Was just there today, (warm,  not hot) mocha expresso was good. I like.  I noticed people from varying age groups.  I am currently not a member of the Co op.  Hope to join

Order food for pickup. Peking chicken fried dumplings and lunch sized cashew chicken. Cashew chicken container with flipped over in the bottom of the basket and most of the sauce that leaked out.  Luckily it was the last thing in the bottom of the bag or it would have covered everything else it was in there. It was enough sauce left in the container to make the cashew chicken edible. I always go to the China Gate for their cashew chicken, and will continue to go back. Things like this happen.
My go to restaurant of Ann Arbor. Amazing food, reasonable prices, great staff. Easy recommend for anyone in the area!

The food is pretty good especially at the price point. The staff was very friendly, and it is great for groups. Portions are pretty big, so there is a chance you will take a box home for your leftovers. Definitely go to China Gate for a good, casual, budget worthy meal with friends.

I've been going to this restaurant on and off for about 7 years. Over the course of this time, they've raised the prices significantly in the qualities dropped a little bit. I've had a lot of different things on their menu which you can get at most Chinese restaurants in the area for cheaper. Yet, their kung pao chicken is very good and that's the only reason I go in there now is to eat that specifically and nothing else. That entree is worth the couple extra dollars to me, even though it's now 40% the more expensive now then it's was four years ago, no big deal. The interior decorations are chintzy and don't expect to use the bathroom while you're there
Great food and reasonable price good staff

Love this place!! Have been here more than once for both sit down and take out. I love it every time. They have a great selection of foods! The staff are super sweet and kind! Never crazy loud in there. Usually only a few tables taken. Recommend to all of my friends! Great local spot!!
Fresh. Quick, & affordable.  Clean, professional atmosphere.  Solid choice for sushi. Would deserve a 5 star rating yet they do not offer alcohol at this time.
This place was marvelous!!! Love the wooden tables and benches. Great food, prices, and service. We are really looking forward to coming back and trying more sushi!
Split several rolls here for lunch. All were good - caterpillar, Ninja, kiss of fire. Quick, attentive service. Casual atmosphere.
If you are looking for a quick bite! Great sushi, nice staff and great service. We will definitely be back.

Food is very delicious - prices are a little high, but you honestly get what you pay for. I do wish the ingredients listed on each item were 100% accurate, I usually have to ask the staff what is in a particular dish and it doesn't always match up with the items listed.
Always fresh, flavorful and delicious! Friendly service and great food.
Fabulous little place, authentic and delicious Syrian cuisine, friendly staff and lots to choose from. Casual.
My chicken shawarma was huge and really flavorful. Large variety of baked goods! Super reasonable prices and great customer service!
Fun place to dine

SIX STARS. I have rarely left a restaurant completely satisfied with my overall experience but this place checked all the boxes. Delicious food. Friendly staff. Clean and aesthetically pleasing. Value for money. Did I mention the delicious food? I had the jerk chicken entree with sauteed veggies and rice & peas. The chicken was top notch - perfectly seasoned and exquisitely cooked. The meat came clean off the bone. My favorite part was the heat: when someone asks me how spicy I want my food, I choose the spiciest option and am typically left disappointed, but I wasn't. The sides were nothing to write home about but they were perfect accompaniments to the chicken. I would definitely come here again and STRONGLY recommend this place to anyone looking for exotic cuisine!
I have not had a good goat dish in years, this place did not disappoint! Also had great service and a unique vibe. I would highly recommend stopping in.

Wife works at Hill, stopped there for lunch. The Jerked Chicken pasta was to die for. So we stopped in over the weekend. Funky little place with get out of your chair and dance food. I had the Jerked chicken cheese fries. (sweet potato) and the curried vegetables.  I mean wow. Ya it was that good.

Lots of choices both traditional and contemporary. All the food is very good as well as dessert. Street parking. Some near garage parking. Spicy, flavorful and plentiful.  Comes mild, medium and hot. Food is always fresh.

Food portions sucked, Sesame chicken had five bite size pieces…and wanton soup was pathetic… one half inch wanton with a dried up piece of pork in a tiny bowl of broth. They do give you a fair amount of vegetable fried rice. Service wasn't great… The only reason i gave it 2 stars is because the chicken/rice tasted pretty good.
Food was good and the wait staff was very friendly. I will be back
Really awful, intensely mediocre food. Skip it lest you waste your money.
Won't reorder. Sweet & Sour Chicken was a very small portion & over cooked.  Egg rolls were very greasy. Pork fried rice had no flavor.  I ended up making my family something different for dinner.
Excellent food and service, quick and efficient and friendly!

so my son and I was watching reruns of Diners, Drive-in and dives when we saw this episode.  my son loves burgers and we wanted to try it. The Service was nice but the Food is horrible. 3 of us ordered burgers and 1 person ordered the chicken sandwich.  we also had onion rinds and fries.  Nothing was good. the Onion rings and fries was cooked in month old oil.  at least that's what they taste like and the burgers and chicken had no favor at all. I had better burgers from just about everywhere.. oh well I went, and I will never go back. I wonder if guy wasn't paid for a good rating.

Great service! Good food! Those fries are to die for!  At least for me.

The do have the customizable soda machine and also they do have the lettuce wrap option for the burger, which they do nicely. I have not tried the shakes.

An absolute classic. If you haven't been, you have to go. 
Beware though, it's a lot of food. Like I eat a lot, but I can only eat maybe a triple and a side of fries. 
Great service, everything is made like right in front of you. You really can't go wrong with anything you get, granted it's pretty limited to burgers and fried foods. 
Make sure you choose a small enough bun, the patty size is deceptive. I got an onion bun on a triple, and there was a lot of bun.

One of my favorite places to bring visitors! A very unique dining expertise with excellent slider-style burgers. I suggest getting Mixed Fried Veggies on the side and many grilled things on your burger (I go with egg, bacon, mushrooms, onions, and salami)

Ann Ann arbor institution since 1953.  One of the best places to get a burger.  You should be polite to the ordering staff or they will tell you to leave.  You need them a lot more than they need you.  Because the burgers are that good.

We have only had Indian food a couple of times. We were super impressed with the atmosphere, service, AND food. The manager personally came to our table and have recommendations based on what we ordered, and was eager to answer any questions we had. The garlic naan was delicious with all of our entrees, and the samosas were a nice start. Would highly recommend to anyone!

Absolutely wonderful! The wait staff was very pleasant & the food was amazing!! The depth of flavors was just outstanding, it was an adventure of culanary artistry. This was my first time eating here, it will not be my last! Both my husband & I were elated with this gem of Ann Arbor.

Being from Toledo, Ohio we (my wife and I) were in Michigan for business acouple of days ago and needed a place to eat. A friend recommended this place so we stopped in for a late lunch. We originally ordered Butter Chicken and another chicken dish that is made with cottage cheese I believe, but I cannot remember the name. Everything was very tasty, so after we ate we ordered a couple other dishes to take home for dinner that night. Today we drove up just to try the buffet we heard about. The buffet is available for only a few hours but it is certainly worth it.

Madras has probably the best lunch buffet in Ann Arbor. It has all the Indian food staples and a good selection of South Indian options. The flavors are very authentic. They also have a Thanksgiving buffet which earns some bonus points from me
Not the best Indian restaurant in Ann Arbor, but it’s a very good option. Especially if you like South Indian food. The people who work here are very nice, too.

I always receive the highest quality customer service from this location. Staff are efficient and friendly. Long phone wait times are a direct result of this location being SO BUSY because the service and food are so great. I can't blame them for being on put on hold - I want the food and obviously I'm not the only one. No Thai on Plymouth Rd is consistently fast and delicious.

In recent years the quality at this particular location has plummeted. Long holds, wrong orders, sub-par food (when compared to other locations). So we go out of our way to go to the better locations in Ann Arbor. It's worth the drive. We give this place a shot about once every 6 months. Most recently I called from the highway to order ahead and pick up on the way home. I was put on hold. 7min 30s later I walked into the store, there was no line, and I was still on hold.  I asked how long they normally have people on hold and the guy behind the counter responds "we've been really busy".  There was no line and the place was half empty. No Thai is great, this particular No Thai is not.

I absolutely adore No Thai - when I'm back in town, it's an absolute MUST to go to. Every single dish is delicious, but I'm extremely fond of the stir fry's paired with tofu. The tofu is a work of art in and of itself - deep fried and fluffy, soaked with their delicious sauce. If you want authentic Thai, you're best going somewhere else -- the food here is highly Americanized. That said, if you're looking for a quick, delicious meal (or even two meals - the portions are huge), this place is a great bet.
Vegetarians beware: the sauces aren't totally vegetarian, so the options might be limited if you avoid things like chicken broth.

Absolutely love this place.    Great food, usually very quick and always friendly.   Sweet and Spicy Chicken with Yoga Flame is my go to.   Always a solid choice.   Drunken Fried Rice (Dim Mak) is always my take home dish for the next day.
Simply my favorite. Remember you can swap sauces between dishes! Easy to find a meal to love.

If you want a pita, this is THE place to go. The pita variety is higher than any other place in A2, and the pitas themselves are the second best in town. It's quick, and you can order ahead. Not a great place to sit down for a date, but for quick food it is number 1. It's totally slept on.
Nice place for a quick bite. I just went there once and there was no one except me. I couple of people came for pickup so I guess that's what it is for. The service was quick and staff is nice.

Makalee pita is the way to go. Perfect combination of pickles, cauliflower and the best garlic sauce in the world. I have been waiting ten years to come back here and it is just as satisfying as the 100 Makalees I ate in undergrad.

The food is good, but the delivery guy was terrible. I ordered food to get delivered in this winter cold weather and the driver refused to bring my food to my apartment and asked me to meet him outside in the parking lot! If I am ordering food for delivery, I am expecting it to come to my door. If you cannot do it, then let me know and I will get my food from somewhere else! If I wanted to get dressed and go out in this cold weather, I would not have ordered delivery!!!!!
Falafel wrap with tabouli is just great!

The people are friendly and loving. The food is awesome and healing,... I like having healthy food that is made from the heart and the soul. Pita, pita ..bread and all kinds of Mediterranean, food is the best diet for me.  I am treated very well and helped with regards to my disabilities. I don't feel like a stranger at Pita Pita. My friends with disabilities, who are  able to take out food or eat inside the restaurant, please try the food and you will feel good after eating. They fill your stomach with good food and they fill your heart and soul with a warmth and Welcome that is remembered even when you're plate is empty.

Some of the best Mediterranean food I've had, and I've been to a fair few Mediterranean countries. The staff is always friendly and wonderful, and they renovated the restaurant a couple years ago; it looks amazing.

They also cater, and were incredibly efficient and professional with the whole process.
This is by far the best chicken ever!  The service is always fast and friendly.  I also recommend this place.  P.s you have to try the garlic spread

Great food, great service, enjoyed the experience. If it's your first time and you've never had this style of food I'd recommend bringing a friend and getting the platter. ( There is a vegetarian option for it)
Friendly staff, but food was very lackluster. I ordered a beef gyro and they microwave reheated what tasted like slow cooker beef. I expected fresh kabob.

Love food but the restaurant itself was disgusting!!!!!!  Horrible looks like floors havent been touched in years bathroom was hideous they should be ashamed of themselves every table had food on it highchairs and booster seats look 40 years old so dirty outside of garbage cans disgusting walls light switches everything is covered in dirt n grime they need to shut down for a day or 2 and do some serious deep cleaning wont come back until they do

We have been receiving delivery service here at the office for a few years.  We order pretty much the same thing each time.  However in today’s order the spinach salad was visibly different – drastically smaller.  I called to question, asking if they changed portions or were we delivered the small vs. the large.  Adamant that the portion did not change and he made no error in prep.  Normally, two of us split the salad.  For $7.99, plus delivery, plus tip - TOTAL rip off.  Horrible customer service - no attempt to resolve.  We will not be ordering from them again.

Was absolutely terrible. Got delivery, didn't receive some of the food I ordered so he just cashed in my money without giving me what I paid for. ON top of it, food quality was terrible and I was sick because of whatever that owner fed me and I had to miss work the next day because of my stomach ache.
I love the fresh salads at Pizza Pino. Very affordable. They have great spring green mixes and awesome toppings like goat cheese, roasted red peppers, cherry tomatoes and bacon crumbles. Yum!
Pizza by the slice was fine. Liked the buffalo.

Amazing for quick burger! Love this place, fresh, hot and quick service. Quality burger,  its not a freeze thawed patty. The only other better burger in town would be Zingermans road house. Forget Culver's too. Love this place!
This was by far the best hot dog I ever ate in my life.  The Hawaiian with the pulled pork and pineapple, and BACON.  Sold.  Must have this in my life again.
Food is expensive and the place is pretty much a hole in the wall, but food was pretty good. Service was slow though

This has been one of my family's favorite places for years. Unfortunately, the quality has definitely dropped.the sausages are much smaller and the toppings less generous than ever before. The prices are a bit lower as they should be. Very disappointing.
Good friendly place.. had Italian Beef.. I enjoyed it and will be back.

Carrier left a package there for me on a Friday. Went to pick it up 2 days later and everyone claimed that it was no where to be found. Unethical way of doing business. Don't accept packages for other people from the post office if you can't properly keep them in a safe place. Will be contacting an attorney regarding this.

Went here for the first time yesterday. Got there around 530 and was able get seated right away. Friendly staff. I ordered the Cap'n Crunch Chicken Tacos and they were AMAZING!!!! Defintely one of my new favorites. Excited go go back and try others.
The food is delicious my favorite is the lobster tacos no coleslaw no cilantro. Excellent place for happy hour food and drink
Reasonably priced lunch specials. Big burritos. Calm atmosphete. Dimly lit but not dark. A good place to watch football games if the bars happen to be too packed. Service was mediocre.

They were short staffed. We were told the wait would be about 20 minutes. The 20 minutes came and went and there was no sign of anyone being ready to seat us, so we ended up leaving without having any food. The 2 stars is only because they had a nice atmosphere.

Delicious food and excellent service! Tonight was our first experience eating Indian cuisine. Our waiter was knowledgeable and friendly with his recommendations and my husband and I both truly enjoyed our experiences.  We would recommend this restaurant to friends and family, and we will definitely be coming back ourselves.
This place was great. We ordered Lamb chops and chicken masala? (The first menu in curry categories) and they were nice. We will visit there again definitely.
The food is amazing and the wait staff so friendly. Every time we are in Ann Arbor we eat there as no other Indian restaurant is as good. We've been eating there for 20 years.

One of the best Indian restaurants I've eaten at and I have been eating there for years. Reminds me of the nicer Indian restaurants in Great Brittan where I first tried Indian food. Authentic food served in a very nice atmosphere. The waiters are all very professional and efficient. I asked about a dish I used to order but was not on the menu now and the waiter said they would make it for me... Chicken Hyderabadi (not sure I spelled that right) delicious! I'll back when I'm in town again.

The food is delicious in every word possible! I went with my mom, and she's usually picky when it comes to food, but she absolutely loved their food. Our waiter was the best! The prices are not that bad. The service was good, a man in a suit (I believe the owner) came to our to check up on us. All in all, it was a great first experience.

I simply love this place. Their ice cream is so great. So many different flavors are available. People who work there are so kind and friendly. The best part of this place is location. Practically right next to Michigan and State movie theater. After the movie, eat in some restaurants in that area but skip the dessert, for dessert come to Michigan Creamery.

A+ ice cream shop. Reasonably-priced and delicious, Michigan Creamery serves products from local Michigan creamers to deliver a local, delicious dessert experience.  Friendly staff help you navigate the wealth of flavor options available to you should be completely overwhelmed. LOTS of options and customization allow you to make a dessert that is completely your own, and keep you coming back for more! Pro tip: free sprinkles when it rains or snows!

My husband got a double dip dish (2 different flavors) and thoroughly enjoyed his ice cream. His favorite was  salted caramel. My daughter and I enjoyed a cup of hot chocolate. It was delicious and quickly warmed us up on this chilly day. We are from out of town and we're very pleased to find a  yummy new ice cream place to visit. We'll definitely be back when we visit Ann Arbor again.
It was good but over priced for what it is. I found the young gentleman who helped us to have a dry personality. Probably won't go back.
Insanely good ice cream!!! Original flavors and a rainy day sprinkles pick you up. Bonus the girls took extra time to pack my to go pint in ice so it would make it back to Hudsonville!!!

Sushi town is a little hole in the wall with possibly the best sushi in Ann Arbor.  Prices are reasonable and the food is delicious. Even getting a carry out they make sure you have what you need. I definitely recommend to anyone that is more concerned about the actual food than the look and ambiance of the establishment. 
Added bonus: Theres a hardware store connected to the building. So if you need a wrench or hammer it's one stop shopping!!!
Best sushi and best service I've ever had. Just amazing.
Don't be fooled by the somewhat shabby digs. The sushi is affordable, of reasonably quality, and the owners/operators are very kind. Some of the best sushi you can get in Ann Arbor.
The food is good the customer service needs HELP

Best sushi I've ever had, and nicest people I've ever encountered in a restaurant. They're always very, very sweet. 

It's a nice environment to sit down and eat, but also located right next to a little park with a picnic table. 

The rolls are big and prices are very low! I LOVE this place! Highly recommend it!
Went here for my birthday. Brandon is EXCEPTIONAL. Hands down best margarita I’ve ever had. He’s so accommodating, professional and friendly!! We’ll be back!

Great Mexican place downtown.  They make the guacamole fresh at your table side.  Good deal on margaritas during happy hour too.  I really like the wet burritos.  My only complaint is that they don't have the tres leches on the dessert menu anymore.   It was my favorite

I feel this was the worst Mexican restaurant I've ever been to. I had specifics on my food and they couldn't even get that right with my allergies and I ate what I'm severely allergic to, only with a swollen throat and itching. The rice was like eating boxed rice, and the beans were not flavored. My 16 yr old daughter said Taco Bell tastes better than Tios. Definitely wasn't worth the drive from Toledo.
Chili con queso is delicious. You can buy individual tacos so you can try a variety of flavors. Fish taco is amazing.
Had the duck mole tamale. Among the best tamales I've ever had. Mole was perfect, complex, and balanced.
Fun place, but lines too long and it feels as if they slow it down to make it look busier.

Refuses to let people in there cause other people think they did something cause other people told them they did something to kick them out and never let them back in again cause of hearsay?  Gotta love Rick's Ann Arbor!!!  I always looked out for you but now!?!?!?

1) They didn’t accept my own ID but the second an underage girl tries to get in while using a *friend’s* ID: it wasn’t a problem. Overly regulatory, elitist, and catering to sexism/rape culture.
2) clearly servicing underage, low life frat/sorority people who thrive off of undiagnosed alcoholism.
3) overpriced. $4.50 for a bud light? Really? 
Ann Arbor should do better. Quit letting people in who ruin the night and upgrade the “bros” that you have checking IDs at the front.

It's good lot of Youth. Should know the game.
Standing in line for over an hour sucks
miss you rick

The new general manager, Emily is horrible! Either she is just plainly rude and has horrible customer service skills or she is racist. I have been frequenting Za's since 2008 and over the years I have had a pretty good experience. It's not the best of food or the worst, but it's pretty good "eats" for the price. 
 Every time I or someone else of color goes to Za's they have a negative encounter with her. Either she does not want to serve us or takes an incredibly long time to get to us, even with no one else in the establishment, or she is just snappy, dismissive and rude. 

Let me be clear, I still like this restaurant and have had a pretty good experience with other staff members, but this little rude one is too much for me. I think I might stop frequenting just because of her consistently rude attitude - I'll take my money somewhere it will be appreciated.

I simply cannot recall a restaurant meal that I've enjoyed so much. In Philadelphia for a brief, last-minute trip, we booked a late dinner at Vetri (last table seated that evening). It was worth staying up for -- every dish was exquisite, especially the famed gnocchi, light as air. And the service was so cheerful, engaged and considerate. Worth every penny and every minute. We may come back to Philly just to eat here again.

Very nice staff and good food and great atmosphere. We didn't care for the Alfredo sauce because it was very, very garlicky. When we mentioned it, and they were happy to bring a new plate with a different sauce!

We were extremely happy with Argiero's!!  My husband and I needed to eat supper before we caught a train and we were in a big hurry.  When we walked in to Argiero's, we were very impressed with the decor and menu.  They were very busy and we thought it would take too long to get served.  When I spoke to the staff, we were seated immediately and they personally helped us with the menu by showing us what entree's would take the least amount of time.  We were skeptical, but decided to stay.  It was literally a matter of a few minutes in which we got served!  The food was excellent!  The bread was so fresh!  I will definitely return to Argiero's during my visits to Ann Arbor.  We were treated like royalty.  Thank you Argiero's!  You made our night!!

This place was phenomenally great.  Argerio's had wonderful service with insightful information about menu items by the wait staff; it is a friendly, warm, and cozy atmosphere with Italian artwork on the walls. The manager even gave me a ride home when he heard I would be venturing home in the subzero freezing weather.  With the great service, the pasta dish I had was the best one I have had in recent memory.  Anyone who loves quality Italian food will especially love this place.

A red sauce Italian-American neighborhood classic.  Don't come here expecting to be reminded of your last visit to Italy, come here to get very good versions of dishes you might have been served 40 or 50 years ago in an Italian restaurant in this country.  No need to go for the fancier stuff on the menu (which can be uneven, although sometimes  good) - the lasagna (meat and meatless), chicken parmesian and even the spaghetti and meatballs are consistently excellent.  Pizza is pretty good, one of the better versions in Ann Arbor.  Meatball sandwich for lunch is a favorite.  Comfort food

Things I like: 
1.   Warm towels to clean my hands before/after dinner 
2.   When you order a feast (good for sharing), you get refills on bread/veggies 
3.  The people (VERY friendly) 
4.  Super fast!  
5.  Lunch prices are VERY reasonable. 

Other thoughts: 
The bread is so-so.   I’ve had better at other places.    Everything in our veg feast was refillable except for the collard greens.  The greens are so yummy...it’s a bummer those can’t be refilled.

I showed up with 3 friends at about 6:45. We were seated quickly, and the server even let us pick the table to sit at. The restaurant was comfortable temperature, with good lighting, and the chairs were also good.

The water at the table was cold and refreshing. I also ordered a tea-cognac which tasted good. The drink was served warm in a glass - the drink certainly tasted good, but I had to let it cool off a bit before I could comfortably lift the hot glass. My group ordered the Ethiopian feast which is basically an all-you-can-eat with each of the entrees. All the entrees were quite good, with reasonable spice levels. Our bread and water was refilled regularly, and the entrees dish
 was also refilled.

The staff was friendly throughout and I had a good time here.

Great place to have a more adventurous meal. We always get the feast, and enjoy the Ethiopian tea and coffee. I'm not a fan of honey wine but theirs is a nice option. We visited again tonight and enjoyed live music with our dinner. The hot hand towels were especially nice on a cold night!

I would give BN 5 stars without hesitation, but I can’t help but feel so wasteful when I get the vegetarian feast and they refill it so generously, but I can’t take what’s leftover. The tea is amazing. Amazing. Go for the tea, at least.
I went with three other people and ordered the vegetarian platter.  We just love our favorite dish.  Waitstaff was fantabulous as always.

Great atmosphere, the interior of the house is adorned with beautiful murals. The one waitress /bartender became overwhelmed by the crowd that followed me. As someone who lived in Germany for a couple of years, I can't speek to the menus authenticity. I had a Reuben that wasn't grilled and the fries lacked any season. A small bit of research will give you insight, I asked for mayo for the fries and was disappointed by the consistency! Surely they could do better, I look forward to a better experience on my next visit.

This place is AMAZING for drinks and food. I'm not a huge beer person, but this place has a ton of cocktails that are strong and delicious.

In terms of food recommendations.

Loved this place the first time we went but this time it was terrible. The food was over cooked to the point that it was hard to chew threw our potato pancakes. The saurbrauten was dried out and chewy as well and tasted like basic beef roast with basic jarred beef gravy on it. For how much we paid for two people, I expected it to be better.

Wow. What an awesome experience. I've heard from a few people that this was great, but it's nice to have confirmed that myself. The main floor is the diner and bar area. The second floor is a mini club/bar, with cover charge, and they even have a basement area, though I was not down there. 

I loved the German pub asthetics and will say it's a nice place to get together with friends for a few beers and such. 

*Do note though, their German food fare is not offered after 10 pm and is not listed on the website as such, but our server was nice enough to still put in our order at 10 minutes after.

I actually like Heidelberg, but after my latest visit it's just so frustrating.  Four reasons are costing them three stars:

1) Service has historically been pretty iffy.  This latest time, our server completely forgot to put in our food order.
2) That would have been fine, but then don't try to blame it on the kitchen.  I don't care how backed up they are, there's no reason 1 appetizer takes an hour, especially when other tables sat later got served first.  Just own it dude.  Oh and don't try to charge me for food I never received.
3) Maybe service would be better overall if management staffed more than 2 bartenders and didn't have 1 of them also wait tables.  On a night of a major football game.  Seriously.
4) Beer prices are really high.  $20 for 3 pints?  What.

Pad See Ew (Medium Spicy, Beef) was phenomenal. The noodles were pretty excellent in texture and taste, the egg/beef/broccolli were cooked just the right amount, and the sauce and spices were fantastic. Medium spice level is not for the faint of heart, so try the lowest level spice first if you don't know what you are getting into. The wait staff is erratic but that wasn't enough to deter from the quality and flavor of the dish!
One of the better Thai spots in the area. Can actually deliver on spiciness if requested. Friendly and quick service, decent parking options nearby.
My first time here. I had the Panang (mild) it was absolutely delicious!! Had chicken satay for appetizer, also very very good. I recommend to all Thai Food lovers

Food was okay. Not the greatest, not the worst. The worst thing about the experience was the decore and the chairs. They were really uncomfortable to sit in and reminded me of the set my grandmother has in her dining room. The decore doesnt match the atmosphere of the restaurant. If i do ever come back, its to order take out.
I ordered the hottest on their menu, result=not hot in the least bit, added my own cayenne pepper, won't order from here again
