Authentic German Food! Cozy place with amazing homemade meals. The bar is well stocked great imported beer. Schnitzel was Perfect! If your in Ann Arbor, do not miss this place!

Even though German food is not my favorite, Metzger's is really quite good. I had the cabbage rolls with egg noodles. Yummy! My nephew had the beef rouland and that was very good. Teeny bit more expensive than I expected it to be. Service was fast and efficient. But my favorite part was their delicious carrot cake for two only $10 for a gigantic piece of carrot cake. It was more than enough for two people to eat so needless to say there was carryout cake. If you like cuckoo clocks and beer steins they have a huge collection you can fawn over.

Used to go to the old restaurant, downtown A. A....not as good now. My friend loved the white fish and her husband the cabbage rolls.  But my meat Pattie was dry and we all agreed the Spaetzle was hard, dry and even the best pieces were chewy.
Delicious, authentic German food. Great beer. Excellent service. Relaxed, family-friendly environment. What more could you want? We're lucky to have this place in Ann Arbor!

I try to stop here for a meal whenever I am in the Ann Arbor area. The food is great and the atmosphere is very friendly.  Schnitzel is awesome and the wurst is the best.  Check out the stein and clock collection!

One of my favorite restaurants in Ann Arbor, good atmosphere and excellent service. Love to start with their monsoon plate, have an upgraded garden salad and then enjoy their seared big eye tuna - an amazing taste explosion. So far their daily specials were always great. They offered a fantastic venison and cooked it to perfection: heavenly tender and super tasty.
Also check out their ginger tea (recipe on their website); perfect drink when it's cold outside.
Ordered tofu and fettuccine,  taste was good but not complex flavor. Small menu with interesting items, but had hard time picking something that sounded appetizing

Perfect in every way. Atmosphere, service, and of course, food were all phenomenal. I really enjoyed my unagi appetizer and sablefish entree. The combination of flavors and textures were superb. The wait staff were great.
Really really great food. Have had this place recommended to me by tons of locals. We went during restaurant week and got a really good deal, both more than satisfied with the food and beer choices.
This place has really great food and the atmosphere is pleasant.  I came here twice for a special occasion and both times I was very satisfied with the service and the food.

Travel to Italy right in downtown Ann Arbor. This restaurant has been a staple of the downtown for years and is always a great experience. High quality servers and fresh ingredients make every dish rich with flavor.
Great Italian food.  They don't have pepperoni for the pizza, but if you ask they have super large sausage similar to pepperoni.  The kids loved eating it.

We went during restaurant week and had their Restaurant Week deal and it was delicious! The portions were smaller because they were only lunch portions for dinner, but they filled us up all the same and we had an appetizer and dessert included in the restaurant week deal! everything was delicious! We were particularly impressed by the olive oil for the bread- it was flavorful and delicious.

It's a hit or miss for this Southern Italian restaurant, it seems. 
Like many, I have been to Palio and walked out with a full and happy stomach, and other times I have left like those unsatisfied. 

The Italian food is something to try if in the area, most of the time it has flavor with lingering effects that dance on your taste-buds, but some other times there is no impression to be found. Prices are high and that makes it hard to decide if you want to come back and get what you've been hearing about or to be let down for poor taste.

The character is romantic: soft lighting, classic music, and deep colors. The oil and bread they serve is very delectable - but make sure to ask for more bread if need be, I have on occasions gotten a plate full of oil and two to three half slices of bread, only for it to be taken away without asking if my party wanted more. The wait staff here is always changing, like anyplace else, so it's hard to say if you will get good service or not.

So if you want to try some very nice Italian food, Palio is a place to seek... only if the timing is right.

Good Italian restaurant in downtown Ann Arbor for large groups. The waiter helped us with our wine selection and overall had excellent service. He made sure that one of my friends who has a nut allergy would not be affected by any of the food on the menu. The food itself was pretty standard for an Italian restaurant in terms of price and taste. The atmosphere allowed for a great sendoff dinner.

Red Hawk is a great place with the feel of a college town restaurant along with a substantial bar. Many of the menu items are kind of offbeat with unusual flavor combinations. However, there are enough mainstream selections to offer something for everyone. My favorite is the salmon pita sandwich topped with thinly sliced marinated cucumber slices with hot pepper flakes. Another favorite is the seafood gumbo soup. The burgers and fries are terrific. If you like nachos with cheese and chili on top, you might want to treat yourself to that item sometime. It's really delicious.

A really great, low-key sort of place. It was warm and welcoming. We had the flank steak meal and a lamb burger. Both were delicious, along with a nice collection of beers to choose from. I'd definitely recommend a stop to this place, especially before going to the State Theatre.
Decent food options and beer list. A bit small but enough room for what it needs to be. Not a bad spot to bring kids with a solid kids menu. Tacos were good, burgers looked better.

Three of us went out for dinner at Red Hawk Bar & Grill on South State Street in Ann Arbor, after the Ann Arbor Film Fest. We loved it - ordered fish and chips (breaded nicely, firm yet tender and so flaky a piece hollowed out a bit when snapped in half), the flank steak, and the salmon entree. They are known for the beer menu here, but a couple of u ordered craft cocktails. This was a good night out with great service!

Good campus choice.  Often crowded.  Good burgers, great Southwest flank steak salad.  Very convenient to University of Michigan events.  They even have menu items that support campus cultural events.  Red Hawk is the kind of place students bring their parents.

AMAZING SERVICE! Everyone is so nice and the FOOD IS AMAZING! I’ve tried almost everything on the menu and everything is so good! Definitely recommend! If you are looking for a really good asian restaurant this is definitely the place. ❤️❤️❤️

I LOVED the pho. One of the best pho I had in my life~ They also have very yummy desserts such as bingsoo/shaved ice! They have great service and also is a friendly place to come with family and friends :)
How do you make a tasteless curry? I'm honestly a little impressed. Didn't know it was possible.

Everything they say about this restaurant is true. Everytime we come in the place is packed and I can see why. They have probably the best Pho anywhere, and the girls that take care of you really go above and beyond for you. Our experience was of 5 stars as service and food as well as the price were awesome. I will definitely come back again and again the next 5 years I'm here at University of Michigan. Great lunch prices and portions, and an excellent place for dinner with groups of friends. Awesome music. Definitely will be back

Service was extremely slow. It took forever for us to get our checks and each step (getting the food, getting the check, getting our cards back) was a pain. I had previously written a very respectful review on their website specifically about this issue, but apparently they did not listen. Very disappointed.

One of the best restaurants in town. By far the best selection of fresh sushi. They have a few hours they do not sell it. They deliver too with Mr. Delivery. The food is always hot fast and fresh. There is times where a reservation may be needed. They get quite busy on Friday and Saturday nights.
Our waitress was very nice and helped us with any questions we had. Nice quiet environment. The food was good!
Great food. We got a meal for two (fine two of us) and there was way too much food. Would recommend an ordering ratio of two meals per three or four people.

The food was excellent. We came in on a very snowy night, so the warm and delicious food was very welcome! The restaurant is a good size and the menu looked very good and authentic Korean. The braised short ribs (gal-bi) were especially delicious. The spicy isn't very spicy, but was still delicious. We didn't try the barbeque, but others around us did and it smelled amazing. We plan to come back and give that a try as well!

Excellent!  My wife and I had lunch here with our boys.  This was my wife’s first time eating Korean food and our server was extremely helpful.  The food was as good as the service.  Highly recommended.

Always the best vegan food! I love that all their options are at least vegetarian, they make going out to eat very easy for vegans, usual it's hard to find a nice restaurant that has options to choose from, not here! Have been there multiple times and haven't had two of the same dishes! They also have meals that are already paired with delicious wines! I highly recommend this spot even if you aren't vegetarian or vegan, they just have delicious food no matter how or what you eat!

Very delicious, although not my favorite place in the area. They were pretty dead and we were there around prime dinner time so we got sat and taken care of immediately. The dessert was quite literally the icing on top. I would go back for just this amazing coconut cake.
Great food.  Large yet intimate space.  Great drink options.  We went during happy hour and enjoyed a meal.  The Gouda Tots are a real treat.

When I walked in, the vibe wasn't super welcoming. There wasn't anyone there to great me and the want a place to be "received", but I was expected to wait to be seated. That made it kind of awkward. Rhett server was friendly enough, but I felt like I was interrupting her from doing something else when she seated me. There were other people there, but it wasn't crowded. It was a Friday afternoon. Once I was deserted and my date served, things went much better. The server spoke highly of our choices when asked what she thought. And, she was correct. Both dished were VERY good. I had the pesto dish and it was perfect! My date had an Asian spicy stirfry l fry with peanuts. It was very tasty as well. I really wish there was a Seva in Toledo Ohio.

I am a meat eater but I went with my friends that don't. I found the place to be very nice. I ordered the baked Mac n cheese. It was very good, I would eat it any day of the week. My buddy got the veggie burger, he cut a small chunk off of it for me and I was very surprised at how much it looked and tasted like real beef. I have tried a couple veggie burgers in the past and this one was by far the best I tasted before. Yam fries were good too. 

While I have no plans to stop eating meat, I would not hesitate on eating here again.

Update: Still love this place! We go there for a special occasion date night and it’s just as delicious as it was 2 years ago!

This place is awesome! The sushi is so fresh and tastes amazing. They have interesting dishes I haven't seen at other places like the "sushi pizza." Everyone working there were super friendly and helpful. I will definitely go back.

I come here often and I spend a decent amount of money here so this last experience is disappointing. I came in and ordered my normal order that’s $20 bucks, I was charged and asked for a side of eel sauce as I always do. This time the lady said there was a .75 cent charge I asked if they changed the policy and she said they always charge for that as if I was lying. I agreed to pay and she then said I couldn’t put .75 cents on a card so I left without it. They lost a regular customer over .75 cents because I won’t be returning. It may seem small but I won’t continue to come to a place that doesn’t value my service!

Great sushi. Also loved the Tempura, and Udon was just perfect. Clean, clear taste without too much sweetness. 
The service is fast and friendly. Lots of space with plenty of parking outside. It was my first visit, but I was told the restaurant improved greatly under the new owner. Highly recommended
I just love this place. The pricing is good and the food is fantastic staff is always friendly
Awesome sushi. Been coming here for years! Sweet potato is my favorite

I love the Chop House. The food is hands down the best in Ann Arbor. We always go for the cheese platter appetizer and it is some of the best you will find. The prices are a little steep but once you taste the food, it is well worth it. The cocktails are alright and they need a bit more mixing before being served as they aren't a uniform flavor but outside of that, I highly recommend this place for an anniversary or birthday or just a nice date. Their cigar lounge is high quality and the atmosphere is perfect. I will always come back to this place.

A couple weeks ago, we enjoyed a dinner elsewhere in Ann Arbor and decided to head to Chop House after for an espresso and cigar. After a half mile walk we arrive to find out the cigar bar is non smoking due to a private party. Fine. No problem, we should have called. Tonight, we did the same thing. Except we called first to make sure the cigar lounge was open, we called, yes it’s open. Perfect, we walk there. Guess what, closed. Continuous bad service from this place. It’s overpriced we all know that, but it used to at least have good service. Not anymore. Save yourself the dull experience and go to the steak house around the corner.

The steaks were tender and thick and all of the appetizers were great. We also had very good service. It's a pretty fancy establishment. And they offer great discounts for birthdays. Roughly enough to make the birthday persons meal free, given that it's on the actual birthday.

Went here on two occasions. One was my girlfriend's birthday. It was a wonderful time. The staff were friendly and very speedy, and food was amazing. However, when I went for my club's business conference, it was a bit hectic-- understandably. Several orders were messed up, but they were corrected surprisingly fast. Overall, a great place to dine!

Pretty awesome place. Went doing restaurant week where you get a 3 course meal or something for $28. I ended up taking my wife for her birthday and got their birthday discount. Got the 11oz steak, calamari, mashed potatoes, and asparagus. All was good. Bathroom was nice and clean but a little intimate since everything is in one little corner. Ambience was great. Recommend seeing Kiara for best service. Overall great experience.

Great food. The salmon burger was nicely cooked and tasted REALLY GOOD.  The garlic bread is also really good. The service is great (they clean very fast, and pick up the crumbs) and the design is nice. Keep up the good work
Great dining experience. Very good entrees, soup, and bread. Laura was a very good server. We got to see the train rumble through too!
Simply Outstanding. The employees are so friendly and the food is excellent. The building is awesome. Everyone makes you feel so welcomed. Love this place

It's a good atmosphere but tables are really close and you can hear peoples conversations around you. I didn't really want to listen to a guy talk about cameras for an hour. Food was good but nothing to brag about would go again but wouldn't care if I never did go back. Seeing the train go by was fun.

Ate hear a few years ago and it was excellent. This place is great for special occasions or even if you're looking to splurge a bit on a great casual dinner.  Outdoor seating is great for sunny days.  Certainly will be coming back, and hope extend my review further!

It was my wife's birthday! I had reservations for a party of ten. It was a Saturday night. We waited a VERY long time for our drinks and bread probably 40-45 minutes. But once they arrived they were amazing. My wife and I had the porterhouse for two and sweet casserole. Sides are a la carte. My steak was absolutely delicious and one of the best I have ever had. My parties entrees ranged from chicken to vegetarian and everyone was blown away by their meal! I did not give them a five purely because of the super long delay at the beginning of service. However you go for the food and that will NOT disappoint! Pricey but worth it!

The cowboy steak is amazing. One of the best steaks I've ever had. That's not hyperbole; it has a great sear, its wonderfully seasoned, and has an amazing flavor. This is a great cut of meat. Truly an excellent experience.

We enjoyed the atmosphere at Knight's newish South U. Location. There is an old school appeal that feels a bit like your  grandfather's favorite steakhouse. I really enjoyed the Cajun Swordfish cooked medium rare.  Our server was friendly, formal, attentive, and knowledgeable.  Overall a nice experience.

One of my favorite places in A2. The staff is wonderful. The food is the best. And I love to sit at the bar and watch the street and meet interesting people and have some drinks. It's the perfect bar to enjoy downtown from and perfect restaurant to have a nice dinner at.
The service mediocre and the food was acceptable. They recently changed their menu and several of my regulars are now missing. Good bye pub burger.

We've eaten at the restaurant once and stayed at the hotel once. Both times were good experiences. When we came for Thanksgiving last year, it was a giant crowd. We ended up waiting a very long time for a table, even with reservations. Once we were seated the food and service were excellent.

One of the best brunch places in Ann Arbor, and at a good price, only $13 all you can eat. The staff were friendly and professional, the place was clean, and the dining area was relaxing. Their prime rib is one of the best I have ever had. They are a family owned hotel and have been in business for a long time. They have really nice rooms and an awesome indoor pool.

I was a guest at the restaurant today. My friend and I enjoyed a delicious brunch and received excellent service. It is a pleasant ambiance and the prices are very reasonable. I will be having a baby shower here in a month and was glad to have the opportunity to enjoy the cuisine!

Loved the decor and the the staff. The cookies waiting upon entry were clutch. Talk about low glucose stopper after a long flight and ride to A2. The restaurant and lounge was even better. This place deserved and truly earned every star. Clean rooms. Spacious and Starbucks coffee in the room!! Awesome. This hotel definitely has fantastic contemporary style.

Enjoyed our stay, especially in the renovated rooms. Seyan at the front desk was so sweet and took great care of us. We loved the chocolate truffle cake given to us for our anniversary. The staff truly made us feel special. And I'd highly recommend the stuffed shrimp for dinner! I only like the lemon drops here, no other is as delicious.

Lovely service. Had the hot bar Sunday am & the frittata was so delicious! Coffee was so delicious.  Used a card & couldn't leave a tip but I was really happy with the service & self serve amenities.  Definitely will be back.
Their bowl of soup is excellent and reasonably priced. Comes with a slice of bread. Best deal in town.
Very kind staff and great coffee and food. Nice atmosphere too.

I enjoy coming here on a Sunday after my yoga class for a matcha latte and a lemon cranberry muffin. I highly recommend both food items. I removed a star because there is only one person working there and while he's nice, he isn't fast and efficient with taking and producing orders. When the line gets long, expect an even longer wait.
Was just there today, (warm,  not hot) mocha expresso was good. I like.  I noticed people from varying age groups.  I am currently not a member of the Co op.  Hope to join

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.
